StackL (R implementation)

StackL.Rd

The StackL function creates a stack. Pure R implementation for benchmarking.

StackL(...)

Usage

StackL(items = NULL)
.$push(item)
.$pop()
.$peek()
.$clear()
.$size()
.$as_list()

Argument

  • items: initialization list

  • item: any R object

See also

Stack

Examples

s <- StackL()
s$push("first")
s$push("second")
s$pop()  # second
#> [1] "second"
s$pop()  # first
#> [1] "first"

s <- stack(list("foo", "bar"))
#> Error in rep.int(factor(names(x), unique(names(x))), lengths(x)): invalid 'times' value
s$push("baz")$push("bla")
